casebody.data: Prather and Others v. Rambo, on Appeal. THE appellants, defendants below, demurred to the declaration, by. writing on the hack of it these-words: “General Demurrer.” The plaintiff’s joinder was, “And Joinder.” Judgment for the plaintiff below. — Held, that the informality of the demurrer could not he assigned for error by the appellants; a party having no right to complain of an error or irregularity produced by his own act. [NO OPINION]
